  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "PT HR Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>This role is a Part time HR Asst supporting the Human Resources Department with clerical and administrative tasks to ensure smooth HR operations.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Post job advertisements accurately to attract suitable candidates for open positions.</li><li>Coordinate interview schedules with candidates and hiring managers to ensure timely recruitment processes.</li><li>Enter and maintain HR data in systems to keep employee records accurate and up to date.</li><li>Prepare onboarding documents and assist with new employee orientation to support smooth integration</li><li>Support various HR initiatives and projects by completing assigned tasks efficiently</li><li>Organize and file HR documents to maintain orderly records and easy retrieval</li><li>Collaborate with team members to complete ad-hoc administrative duties as needed.</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum 1 year experience in HR functions</li><li>Minimum Diploma in Human Resources or related disciplines.</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office applications to complete administrative tasks effectively</li><li>Strong communication skills in English to interact clearly with colleagues and candidates.</li><li>Proactive attitude and willingness to take on new challenges.</li><li>Pleasant personality and ability to work well within a team environment.</li></ul><p>Able to commit for 6 months to 1 year.<br />Hybrid work arrangement<br />Office in Tanjong Pagar</p>",
